{"parse":{"title":"Mark Liberman","pageid":6917171,"revid":841407796,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Mark Liberman</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span class=\"nickname\">Mark Yoffe Liberman</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma&#160;mater</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/MIT\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MIT\">MIT</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Fields</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">Linguistics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania\" title=\"University of Pennsylvania\">University of Pennsylvania</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Thesis\" title=\"Thesis\">Thesis</a></th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ai.mit.edu/projects/dm/theses/liberman75.pdf\"><i>The intonational system of English (PhD)</i></a>&#160;<span style=\"font-size:97%;\">(1975)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Influences</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Alvin_Liberman\" title=\"Alvin Liberman\">Alvin Liberman</a> (father)<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Isabelle_Liberman\" title=\"Isabelle Liberman\">Isabelle Liberman</a> (mother)</td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Mark Yoffe Liberman</b> <span class=\"nowrap\"><span class=\"IPA nopopups noexcerpt\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:IPA/English\" title=\"Help:IPA/English\">/<span style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\"><span title=\"/\u02c8/: primary stress follows\">\u02c8</span><span title=\"&#39;l&#39; in &#39;lie&#39;\">l</span><span title=\"/\u026a/: &#39;i&#39; in &#39;kit&#39;\">\u026a</span><span title=\"&#39;b&#39; in &#39;buy&#39;\">b</span><span title=\"/\u0259r/: &#39;er&#39; in &#39;letter&#39;\">\u0259r</span><span title=\"&#39;m&#39; in &#39;my&#39;\">m</span><span title=\"/\u0259n/: &#39;on&#39; in &#39;button&#39;\">\u0259n</span></span>/</a></span></span><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is an American <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">linguist</a>.  He has a dual appointment at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania\" title=\"University of Pennsylvania\">University of Pennsylvania</a>, as Trustee Professor of Phonetics in the Department of Linguistics, and as a professor in the Department of Computer and Information Sciences. He is the founder and director of the <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistic_Data_Consortium\" title=\"Linguistic Data Consortium\">Linguistic Data Consortium</a>.   Liberman is the Faculty Director of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ware_College_House&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ware College House (page does not exist)\">Ware College House</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania\" title=\"University of Pennsylvania\">University of Pennsylvania</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Research\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Research</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Mobile_phones_and_endangered_languages\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mobile phones and endangered languages</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Books\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Liberman is the son of the late <a href=\"/wiki/Alvin_Liberman\" title=\"Alvin Liberman\">Alvin Liberman</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Isabelle_Liberman\" title=\"Isabelle Liberman\">Isabelle Liberman</a>. Both were psychologists.\n</p><p>Mark Liberman attended <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_College\" title=\"Harvard College\">Harvard College</a> but did not graduate. After two years' service in the <a href=\"/wiki/US_Army\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"US Army\">US Army</a> in Vietnam,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> he enrolled in graduate school in <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">linguistics</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/MIT\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MIT\">MIT</a>, from which he received a <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\">Master of Arts</a> and, in 1975, a <a href=\"/wiki/PhD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PhD\">PhD</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>From 1975 to 1990, he was a Member of Technical Staff at <a href=\"/wiki/Bell_Laboratories\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bell Laboratories\">Bell Laboratories</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Research\">Research</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Research\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Liberman's main research interests lie in <a href=\"/wiki/Phonetics\" title=\"Phonetics\">phonetics</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Prosody_(linguistics)\" title=\"Prosody (linguistics)\">prosody</a>, and other aspects of <a href=\"/wiki/Speech_communication\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Speech communication\">speech communication</a>. His early research established the linguistic subfield of <a href=\"/wiki/Metrical_phonology\" title=\"Metrical phonology\">metrical phonology</a>. Much of his current research is conducted through <a href=\"/wiki/Computational_linguistics\" title=\"Computational linguistics\">computational</a> analyses of linguistic <a href=\"/wiki/Corpus_linguistics\" title=\"Corpus linguistics\">corpora</a>. In 2017, Liberman was the recipient of the <a href=\"/wiki/IEEE_James_L._Flanagan_Speech_and_Audio_Processing_Award\" title=\"IEEE James L. Flanagan Speech and Audio Processing Award\">IEEE James L. Flanagan Speech and Audio Processing Award</a>.\n</p><p>Liberman is also the founder of (and frequent contributor to) <a href=\"/wiki/Language_Log\" title=\"Language Log\">Language Log</a>, a blog with a broad cast of dozens of professional linguists. The concept of the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Eggcorn\" title=\"Eggcorn\">eggcorn</a></i> was first proposed in one of his posts there.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mobile_phones_and_endangered_languages\">Mobile phones and endangered languages</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Mobile phones and endangered languages\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2012, Liberman and Steven Bird began a US$101,501 project \"to use <a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_phone\" title=\"Mobile phone\">mobile telephones</a> to collect larger amounts of data on undocumented <a href=\"/wiki/Endangered_languages\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Endangered languages\">endangered languages</a> than would ever be possible through usual fieldwork.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The project resulted in the <a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_app\" title=\"Mobile app\">mobile app</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Aikuma\" title=\"Aikuma\">Aikuma</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Mark Liberman and <a href=\"/wiki/Geoffrey_K._Pullum\" title=\"Geoffrey K. Pullum\">Geoffrey K. Pullum</a>, <i>Far from the Madding Gerund: and Other Dispatches from the Language Log</i>. 2006, William, James, and Co. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-59028-055-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-59028-055-5\">1-59028-055-5</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mark_Liberman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Mark Liberman (2014-09-17). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll/?p=14653\">\"UM / UH map in the media\"</a>. <i>Language Log</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-10-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Language+Log&amp;rft.atitle=UM+%2F+UH+map+in+the+media&amp;rft.date=2014-09-17&amp;rft.au=Mark+Liberman&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Flanguagelog.ldc.upenn.edu%2Fnll%2F%3Fp%3D14653&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMark+Liberman\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://normblog.typepad.com/normblog/2007/06/the-normblog-pr.html\">normblog: The normblog profile 196: Mark Liberman</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" clas